nodes.title: Instructions
widgets_values:
-- Wan Restyle --

Step 1: Load the reference video you want to use, the best results come from videos where the subject is clear for as much of the video as possible.

Step 2: Activate Image2Image workflow, add your prompt to that workflow and generate a starting image, once complete and you are happy with the output, right click and select "Copy (Clipspace)". This part is optional if you already have an image you want to start with, but for the best results try to have an image that matches the start frame of the reference video as much as possible, otherwise there will be a morph to get it to match the video.

Step 3: Activate Video2Video + Style workflow, right click on "Load Image: Start Image" and select "Paste (Clipspace) if you generated from Text2Image, otherwise upload your desired start image. Choose your desired resolution, if generating at 480p on an Ultra machine (48gb VRAM), you can generate up to 81 frames, for 720p the max is 51 frames, you set this in the "frame_load_cap" on the reference video. Set your prompt, if you generated from Image2Image it can be similar to that prompt but make sure to add anything you feel it might need to describe a video instead of just an image. Hit Generate!

*If copy (clipspace) does not work just do manual save image and load image.

nodes.title: Preprocessor Guide
widgets_values:
Choose the best preprocessor for what you are trying to generate.

If the reference video is focused on a human subject, it is best to use Depth+OpenPose (default).

If it is a non-human subject, use Depth only.

If it is any type of subject but your goal is to only transfer a style while keeping the output as close to the original video as possible (for example, turning the reference video into a cartoon style video), try using Scribble.
